for opening configuaration file type the below command:

urlwatch --edit

for closing file presss 

Ctrl+x

for saving the file press
ctrl+s

for adding website type the below command
urlwatch --add url=http://example.org,name=Example


how to add a website: 
just type the command:

urlwatch --edit

then a file will open in front of you:

type
 
---
kind: url
name: name_of_your_website
url: urllink_example.com
filter: element-by-class:class_name,html2text




for watching the url list:
type
urlwatch --list


for testing a website:
type
urlwatch --test-filter number_of_the_url

example: urlwatch --test-filter 1 

for getting the number type:
urlwatch --list

result:
1: GitHub (https://github.com/Traideas/Docx/edit/main/README.md/)
2: GDPRTableOfContents (https://ico.org.uk/for-organisations/guide-to-the-general-data-protection-regulation-gdpr/)
3: Introduction (https://ico.org.uk/for-organisations/guide-to-the-general-data-protection-regulation-gdpr/)
4: bikroy.com (https://bikroy.com/bn/ads/dhaka/vehicles)
5: franz-immobilien (https://www.franz-immobilien.com/Eigentumswohnungen.htm)


They are the urls.


1,2,3,4... are the url number here. 
example: urlwatch --test-filter 1 
for testing 1. GitHub website 

